  <summary date="2015-03-03T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Personal Health Investment Today Act or the PHIT Act 

Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a medical care tax deduction for up to $1,000 ($2,000 for a joint return or a head of household) of qualified sports and fitness expenses. Defines "qualified sports and fitness expenses" as amounts paid for fitness facility memberships, physical exercise programs, and exercise equipment.</summary>
